{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 12:40:10.281698", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of submission\n- is_anomaly: true\n- Faulty devices: leaf_router_0_0 (primary), pc_0_0 (impacted host)\n- Root cause selected: bgp_blackhole_route_leak\n\nNotes / recommended next steps (optional)\n- On leaf_router_0_0:\n  - Inspect kernel route entries (e.g., ip route show table main) and remove the blackhole for 10.0.0.0/24, replacing it with the connected route if needed (e.g., ip route del blackhole 10.0.0.0/24; ip addr add/ensure 10.0.0.1/24 on eth8).\n  - Check FRR configuration for any network statements or route filters that might have installed the blackhole and correct them.\n  - Restart or reconcile FRR if necessary after fixing kernel routes.\n- Validate by pinging 10.0.0.2 from other routers and verifying the connected route is present.\n- Optionally gather additional logs (kernel RTM messages, FRR logs) to determine why the blackhole was installed to prevent recurrence.\n\nIf you want, I can now run commands to collect the specific kernel route entries and FRR config snippets or craft exact CLI commands for remediation.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2322, "output_tokens": 270, "total_tokens": 2592, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
